The paper proposes a framework for neural network-based reasoning over natural language sentences, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories in computer science. Given that the paper deals with natural language processing and deep learning, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, since the paper involves reasoning and inference, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also mentions a specific interaction-pooling mechanism and a deep architecture, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, since the paper deals with natural language sentences, it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it involves understanding and processing textual information.
